  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for the Expansion of Social Protection Programmes</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The programme aims to intensify the impact of Finland&apos;s development efforts within the primary goal of the development policy programme, poverty eradication, and in the cross-cutting themes of gender equality and vulnerable groups. At the same time, the programme supports the efforts of Zambia to attain the status of a middle-income country, where extreme poverty has been eradicated. It aims to reduce poverty, hunger and chronic malnutrition especially in the rural areas by implementing previously succesfully piloted family grant and child grant models and developing employment pension and social pension schemes. The programme also strengthens the capacities of the Ministry of Community Development and Social Services (MCDSS) and Ministry of Labour and Social Security (MLSS) implementing the programme. The programme has potential to evolve into a sectoral budget support programme.</narrative>
  </description>
